   stability of the banking system. Financial integration allows banks in
   different regions to smooth local liquidity shocks by borrowing and
   lending on a world interbank market. We show under which conditions
   financial integration induces banks to reduce their liquidity holdings
   and to shift their portfolios toward more profitable but less liquid
