   game. It is known that the core of the newsvendor game is nonempty, and
   one can use duality theory in stochastic programming to construct an
   allocation-referred to as the dual-based allocation-belonging to the
   core. Yet, an allocation that lies in the core does not necessarily
   guarantee the unhindered formation of a coalition, as some existing
   members' allocated costs may increase when new members are added in the
   process. In this work, we use the concept of population monotonic
   allocation scheme (PMAS), which requires the cost allocated to every
   member of a coalition to decrease as the coalition grows, to study
   allocation schemes in a growing population. We show that when the
