   architecture-induced changes in upstream choices. These findings call
   into question both policy makers' and industry advocates' reliance on
   choice-based privacy protection mechanisms, contribute to an emerging
   behavioral perspective on privacy decision making, and highlight the
   importance of accounting for the cascaded nature of privacy decision
