   linear dynamics, simple contracts are sufficient; (ii) when the market
   is continuous, the quantity distortion should be pervasive; and (iii)
   when the market is nonstationary, the distortion can vanish, intensify,
   stay constant, or even go nonmonotonic over time. By highlighting the
   central role of realistic market behaviors, this paper advances our
   understanding of channel theory and practice.
