   perfect and, more realistically, bounded rationality. In addition to the
   classical profit-maximizing firm unconstrained by ethics, we model an
   ethically constrained (but otherwise profit-maximizing) firm that honors
   its contractual obligations irrespective of legal restraints. We prove
